refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
&style.oop;
public DateTimeDateTime::setISODate intyear intweek intday1
&style.procedural;
DateTimedate_isodate_set DateTimeobject intyear intweek intday1
Configure une date au format ISO 8601 : en utilisant des décalages de semaines et de jours, au lieu de dates spécifiques.

  &reftitle.examples;

   Exemple avec DateTime::setISODate

&style.oop;


<?php
$date = new DateTime();

$date->setISODate(2008, 2);
echo $date->format('Y-m-d') . "\n";

$date->setISODate(2008, 2, 7);
echo $date->format('Y-m-d') . "\n";
?>



&style.procedural;


<?php
$date = date_create();

date_isodate_set($date, 2008, 2);
echo date_format($date, 'Y-m-d') . "\n";

date_isodate_set($date, 2008, 2, 7);
echo date_format($date, 'Y-m-d') . "\n";
?>


   &examples.outputs;


2008-01-07
2008-01-13




   Les valeurs qui excèdent leur bornes s'ajoutent à leur parent


<?php
$date = new DateTime();

$date->setISODate(2008, 2, 7);
echo $date->format('Y-m-d') . "\n";

$date->setISODate(2008, 2, 8);
echo $date->format('Y-m-d') . "\n";

$date->setISODate(2008, 53, 7);
echo $date->format('Y-m-d') . "\n";
?>


   &example.outputs;


2008-01-13
2008-01-14
2009-01-04




   Calcul du mois dans lequel est une semaine


<?php
$date = new DateTime();
$date->setISODate(2008, 14);
echo $date->format('n');
?>


   &examples.outputs;


3
